01:18:17.990 --> 01:18:21.540
water minus rho ping pong ball.

01:18:21.540 --> 01:18:23.250
And I can write this
as the volume times

01:18:23.250 --> 01:18:25.180
rho water is 12 rho
ping pong balls,

01:18:25.180 --> 01:18:27.510
so that's 12 minus 1
rho ping pong ball.

01:18:27.510 --> 01:18:31.550
That's 11 rho ping pong ball.

01:18:31.550 --> 01:18:35.350
But this is equal to 11
times the weight of the ping

01:18:35.350 --> 01:18:39.450
pong ball-- oh sorry-- 11 times
the mass of the ping pong ball.

01:18:39.450 --> 01:18:40.700
The volume times the density.

01:18:40.700 --> 01:18:42.630
So, mass ping pong ball.

01:18:42.630 --> 01:18:45.160
Now, there's an important thing
that I forgot to add here,

01:18:45.160 --> 01:18:47.270
what did I forget to add?

01:18:47.270 --> 01:18:48.000
G. Right?

01:18:48.000 --> 01:18:50.726
It's the force is
the mass times g.

01:18:50.726 --> 01:18:54.470
OK, g, g, and g.

01:18:54.470 --> 01:18:58.399
So, we get that the force is
equal to 11 m ping pong ball g.

01:18:58.399 --> 01:18:59.440
Everyone agree with that?

01:18:59.440 --> 01:19:01.030
I haven't done anything sneaky.

01:19:01.030 --> 01:19:02.920
And so, as a consequence,
what this predicts

01:19:02.920 --> 01:19:05.190
is that if I take the
force and I divide it

01:19:05.190 --> 01:19:07.100
by the mass of the
ping pong ball,

01:19:07.100 --> 01:19:10.040
I get 11 times the
acceleration of gravity.

01:19:10.040 --> 01:19:12.590
And here's what that predicts,
that predicts that when I let

01:19:12.590 --> 01:19:16.710
go of this thing,
what should happen?

01:19:16.710 --> 01:19:19.410
It should accelerate
upward through the water

01:19:19.410 --> 01:19:22.360
at 11 times the acceleration
of gravity, which

01:19:22.360 --> 01:19:25.100
is roughly 10 meters
per second squared.

01:19:25.100 --> 01:19:26.920
So, 110 meters per
