01:21:02.820 --> 01:21:05.054
So, what's going on?

01:21:05.054 --> 01:21:07.747
AUDIENCE: [INAUDIBLE].

01:21:07.747 --> 01:21:09.330
PROFESSOR: OK, so
here's the question.

01:21:09.330 --> 01:21:11.788
Has a mass of the ping pong
ball, my empty little ping pong

01:21:11.788 --> 01:21:13.620
ball changed?

01:21:13.620 --> 01:21:16.324
So, something like
that has to be true.

01:21:16.324 --> 01:21:17.490
But what's the right answer?

01:21:17.490 --> 01:21:21.330
The right answer is this,
the thing that's moving,

01:21:21.330 --> 01:21:23.970
is not the ping pong ball.

01:21:23.970 --> 01:21:26.100
The ping pong ball is
interacting with the fluid.

01:21:26.100 --> 01:21:28.020
And as a ping pong
ball accelerates,

01:21:28.020 --> 01:21:30.190
it drags the fluid
along with it.

01:21:30.190 --> 01:21:31.810
And as it goes
faster, and faster,

01:21:31.810 --> 01:21:34.239
it drags more and more of
the fluid along with it.

01:21:34.239 --> 01:21:36.280
And as it's dragging more
and more of that fluid,

01:21:36.280 --> 01:21:38.241
the effective mass
of the entire object

01:21:38.241 --> 01:21:39.990
that's moving-- which
is now the ping pong

01:21:39.990 --> 01:21:44.300
ball, and all of its associated
water-- is increasing.

01:21:44.300 --> 01:21:47.040
And now, if you take that force,
which was constant, and divide

01:21:47.040 --> 01:21:49.010
by this growing
effective mass, you

01:21:49.010 --> 01:21:51.777
find that the acceleration
rapidly falls off.

01:21:51.777 --> 01:21:53.110
And you get a terminal velocity.

01:21:53.110 --> 01:21:54.050
And you know this
works, because if you

01:21:54.050 --> 01:21:56.150
blow a bubble under water,
it doesn't shoot upwards

01:21:56.150 --> 01:21:57.400
with an infinite acceleration.

01:21:57.400 --> 01:21:59.020
It goes glurg, glurg, glurg.

01:21:59.020 --> 01:22:02.930
And this idea, this idea
of the effective mass

01:22:02.930 --> 01:22:05.640
of a particle changing
with its state of motion,

01:22:05.640 --> 01:22:08.070
is an idea called
renormalization.

01:22:08.070 --> 01:22:10.690
And it plays an essential role,
not just in particle physics,

01:22:10.690 --> 01:22:13.140
but in all of modern
condensed matter physics.

